<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Adopt" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Adopt,</orth> 1) to receive to the place of a child: <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.191" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 191</bibl>. Joined with <emph>heir</emph>: <cit><quote>to be --ed heir to Frederick,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 2, 246</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.135" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 135</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.98" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 98</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.88" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 88</bibl>.<lb />2) to receive as one's own what is not so naturally: <cit><quote>a Roman now --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 1.463" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 463</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>an --ed name,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 2, 18</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>which you a. your policy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 2, 48</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>new --ed to our hate,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.206" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 206</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>